Charles de Gaulle Airport to Paris: Complete 2025 Guide to Taxi, Uber, Bolt, Private Transfer & Low-Cost Train Services

Landing at Charles de Gaulle Airport (CDG), one of Europe’s busiest airports, is both exciting and overwhelming—especially if it’s your first time in Paris. Fortunately, getting from the airport to the heart of Paris is simple once you know your options. Whether you prefer a taxi, Uber, Bolt, a private transfer, or the low-cost train service, this guide will help you choose the transport that matches your budget and travel style.

1. Taxi From Charles de Gaulle Airport to Paris

Taking a taxi is one of the easiest and most stress-free ways to reach Paris from CDG. Paris airport taxis have regulated flat rates, so you know the price before starting the journey.

Taxi Flat Rates (Official Tariffs) https://www.transfer-private.com/

CDG → Right Bank (North of the Seine): €62

CDG → Left Bank (South of the Seine): €55

These prices include all passengers and luggage, making taxis an excellent option for families or couples with heavy bags.

Where to Find Taxis at CDG

Official taxi stands are located outside every terminal. Follow signs reading “Taxis”. Ignore anyone offering taxi services inside the terminal—only official Paris taxis are permitted.

Travel Time

45–70 minutes, depending on traffic
During rush hour (7–9 AM and 4–7 PM), allow extra time.

Why Choose a Taxi?

Door-to-door convenience

Flat rate = no surprises

24/7 availability

Perfect for late-night arrivals or if you’re tired after a long flight

2. Private Transfer From Charles de Gaulle to Paris

If you want total convenience, a private transfer is the most comfortable option. These services can be pre-booked online, and a professional driver will meet you inside the arrival hall holding your name sign.

What Makes Private Transfers Popular?

Guaranteed pickup time

Fixed pricing (usually €55–€90 depending on vehicle type)

Larger vehicles available for groups

No waiting in taxi lines

Multilingual drivers

This option is ideal for business travelers, families, or anyone who prefers a smooth, premium travel experience.

Travel Time

40–60 minutes to central Paris

Private transfers provide a calm, easy start to your Paris trip, especially after a long-haul flight.

3. Uber Taxi From CDG to Paris

Ridesharing apps like Uber operate at Charles de Gaulle Airport, offering several service levels depending on your comfort and budget.

Typical Uber Prices From CDG

UberX: €45–€60

Uber Green: €45–€60

Uber Berline (luxury): €75–€120

Prices can vary depending on demand and time of day. During peak hours, you may pay more than the flat-rate official taxi price.

Where to Meet Your Uber Driver

The app will direct you to designated pickup zones at your terminal. These areas are clearly marked and easy to locate.

Why Choose Uber?

Transparent pricing

No need for cash

Ability to choose the vehicle type

Track your ride in real-time

Uber is a good alternative to taxis, especially for travelers who already use the app regularly.

4. Bolt From Charles de Gaulle to Paris

Bolt, another popular ride-hailing service in Paris, is often slightly cheaper than Uber. Many travelers choose Bolt for budget-friendly rides without sacrificing convenience.

Typical Bolt Prices From CDG

Bolt: €40–€55

Comfort: €50–€70

Premium: €70–€110

Bolt usually offers competitive prices, especially during off-peak hours. For solo travelers or couples, it can be a smart, cost-efficient choice.

Why Choose Bolt?

Often cheaper than Uber

Quick pickup times

Easy app interface

Multiple ride categories

If cost matters, Bolt may be your best rideshare option.

5. Low-Cost Train Service: RER B From CDG to Paris

If you’re looking for the cheapest and fastest way to get from Charles de Gaulle Airport to Paris, the RER B train is unbeatable.

RER B Ticket Price

€11.45 per adult

Children 4–10: Reduced fare

Under 4: Free

Travel Time

35–45 minutes

Where to Board the RER B

CDG has two RER stations:

Aéroport Charles de Gaulle 1 (for Terminals 1 & 3)

Aéroport Charles de Gaulle 2 – TGV (for Terminal 2)

Follow signs reading “Paris by Train / RER B.”

Major Stops in Paris

The RER B takes you to key stations:

Gare du Nord

Châtelet–Les Halles

Saint-Michel Notre-Dame

Denfert-Rochereau

From these stops, you can easily connect to the Paris Metro.

Why Choose the RER B?

Cheapest option

Fastest arrival in central Paris

Avoids road traffic
Perfect for backpackers, solo travelers, or anyone on a budget.

Final Tips for Traveling From Charles de Gaulle to Paris

Avoid unofficial taxi offers inside the terminal.

If traveling during rush hour, trains may be faster than cars.

For the easiest experience, book a private transfer ahead of time.

Uber and Bolt are great alternatives but can surge in price.

If budget is your priority, choose the RER B train.

Getting from Charles de Gaulle Airport to Paris is simple once you choose the transport option that matches your needs. Whether you prefer the convenience of a taxi, the comfort of a private transfer, the affordability of the train, or the flexibility of Uber and Bolt, you’ll reach Paris smoothly and start enjoying the city in no time. Bon voyage!


